  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Resident Technical Officer (Civil & Structural)",
  "description": "<p><strong>Resident Technical Officer (Civil & Structural)</strong></p><p>* Diploma in Civil Engineering or equivalent from Singapore</p><p>Polytechnic or other tertiary institutions of equivalent</p><p>standing;</p><p>* Registered as Resident Technical Officer with BCA/IES/</p><p>ACES; and</p><p>* At least 5 years of site supervision experience as Resident</p><p>Technical Officer.</p><p>* National Certificate on Construction Supervision from BCA</p><p>Academy or equivalent.</p><p>In addition to the qualifications, site supervision and practical experience as</p><p>specified, all Site Supervisors shall also possess the following competencies and</p><p>personal attributes:</p><p>* technically strong, able to review design details, method statements and use</p><p>sound judgment to resolve site issues during the course of construction works;</p><p>*conversant with local building codes and regulations, authority requirements</p><p>and practices;</p><p>* attended minimally 1 safety course & demonstrate safety acumen to highlight</p><p>potential safety infringements/unsafe practices on site;</p><p>* demonstrate maturity and ability to manage a team of Site Supervisors</p><p>* possible good communication and inter-personal skills, and able to work as a</p><p>team player;</p><p>* diligent, methodical, meticulous and willing to work overtime; and</p><p>* keen learner and supportive of digitalisation efforts in projects.</p><p>* Relevant experience refers to the necessary site supervision / practical experience and skills set that the site supervisor possesses to supervise the construction of the civil / structural / mechanical and electrical / architectural works of the project(s) to which he is to be assigned to.</p>",
  "minimumYearsExperience": 5,
